hod on a dataset of 13 abundances\nmeasured in the spectra of 187,000 stars by the GALAH survey. We recover 7 of\nthe 9 observed clusters (6 globular and 3 open clusters) in chemical space with\nminimal contamination from field stars and low numbers of outliers. With\nchemical tagging, we also identify two Pleiades supercluster members (which we\nconfirm kinematically), one as far as 6$^\\circ$ -- one tidal radius away from\nthe cluster centre.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Sep 2017 02:57:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-06"}
